10. mr-mime.ts: export const MR_MIME, key:'mr-mime', name:'Mr. Mime', sprite:SPRITES.mrMime, hp:60, speed:35, damage:8, xpValue:120, scale:1.0, behavior:'shielder'
11. hitmonlee.ts: key:'hitmonlee', name:'Hitmonlee', sprite:SPRITES.hitmonlee, hp:90, speed:30, damage:40, xpValue:100, scale:1.1, behavior:'leaper'
12. electabuzz.ts: key:'electabuzz', name:'Electabuzz', sprite:SPRITES.electabuzz, hp:100, speed:85, damage:15, xpValue:95, scale:1.1, behavior:'stunner', contactEffect:{type:'stun', durationMs:500}

In index.ts add imports and register all 12 in ENEMIES. Use sections: '// ── Phase 3 novos ──' and '// ── Phase 4 novos ──'.
For mr-mime.ts: export const MR_MIME, import { MR_MIME }, register as 'mr-mime': MR_MIME.

In `src/systems/EnemyBehaviors.ts`, implement puller (Magnemite) and pullerElite (Magneton).

puller: PULL_FORCE=15, PULL_RANGE=150. Each frame: move toward player normally. If dist<=PULL_RANGE, apply pull on player body velocity (direction from player TO enemy, normalized * PULL_FORCE * delta/1000). VFX guard: tint pulse 0x44aaff.

pullerElite: PULL_FORCE_ELITE=30, PULL_RANGE_ELITE=200. Same pull but stronger. State key pe_nextWave. Every 5000ms if player within 120px: apply stun 300ms. Look for player.applyStun() or player.applyContactEffect() method. If no direct method, just skip stun and add TODO. VFX: tint 0xffff44 for 200ms.

Player body access: const playerBody = player.body as Phaser.Physics.Arcade.Body | null; if (!playerBody) return;
Enemy body access: const body = enemy.body as Phaser.Physics.Arcade.Body | null; if (!body) return;

Movement: angle = Phaser.Math.Angle.Between(enemy.x, enemy.y, player.x, player.y); body.velocity.x = Math.cos(angle) * enemy.speed; body.velocity.y = Math.sin(angle) * enemy.speed;

Add both cases to updateBehavior switch.

In `src/systems/EnemyBehaviors.ts`, implement trapper (Tentacool) and trapperElite (Tentacruel).

These are simple — the stun contactEffect is applied automatically on collision. The behavior just adds movement + visual feedback.

trapper: Move toward player normally. VFX guard: permanent tint 0x44ffaa.
trapperElite: Move toward player normally. VFX guard: permanent tint 0xff4444.

Movement pattern:
  const body = enemy.body as Phaser.Physics.Arcade.Body | null; if (!body) return;
  const angle = Phaser.Math.Angle.Between(enemy.x, enemy.y, player.x, player.y);
  body.velocity.x = Math.cos(angle) * enemy.speed;
  body.velocity.y = Math.sin(angle) * enemy.speed;

Add both cases to updateBehavior switch.

Implement shielder behavior (Mr. Mime) in EnemyBehaviors.ts AND shield check in Enemy.ts.

shielder behavior:
Constants: SHIELDER_COOLDOWN=6000, SHIELDER_DURATION=3000, SHIELDER_RANGE=150.
State key: sh_nextShield.
Move toward player normally. Every COOLDOWN ms: use getSpatialGrid().queryRadius(enemy.x, enemy.y, RANGE) to find nearest non-boss active unshielded ally. Apply shield: target.data.set('shielded',true), target.data.set('shieldEnd',time+DURATION). VFX: target.setTint(0x4488ff).

Shield check in Enemy.takeDamage() (src/entities/Enemy.ts):
At TOP of takeDamage method, BEFORE existing checks:
  const shieldEnd = this.data.get('shieldEnd') as number | undefined;
  if (shieldEnd && this.scene && this.scene.time.now < shieldEnd) {
    this.setTint(0x4488ff);
    this.scene.time.delayedCall(150, () => { if (this.active) this.clearTint(); });
    return false;
  }
  if (this.data.get('shielded')) {
    if (!shieldEnd || (this.scene && this.scene.time.now >= shieldEnd)) {
      this.data.set('shielded', false);
      if (this.active) this.clearTint();
    }
  }

Import getSpatialGrid in EnemyBehaviors if not already imported. Do NOT shield bosses or self.
